cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.DB 

The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to solve the problem of author name normalization in e-commerce catalogs. This falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with search and recommendation systems. The use of neural networks for natural language processing suggests the paper could also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques for sequence-to-sequence learning and Siamese neural networks suggests the paper could also belong to the deep learning (cs.DL) sub-category. Finally, the use of open data sources and the need to handle large amounts of data suggests the paper could also belong to the databases (cs.DB) sub-category.
